title: For Sale:  Davis Industries P32 Auto-pistol, USA-Made,  "A Good Kind of Clunky"
postcontent: "A Good Kind of Clunky" - This is an original Davis Industries P-32 Auto-pistol, whose designs and rights were bought by Cobra in 1998 and who continues to make the P-32 as the CA-32, to this day. ABOUT THE GUN:  Zinc allow is dense and heavy, and to stand up to firearms use, you have to use a lot of it, so the P-32 is heavy - 22 ounces - to the point of being clunky.  But it's a GOOD KIND OF CLUNKY.  There is a satisying feel and heft to it when you handle the weapon. The mag hold six .32 ACP rounds and is secured by a rather robust European style heel release. A strong mainspring coupled with a dense slide make chambering a round a breeze, and the oversized extractor will fling even a loaded round nearly 2 ft.  The trigger is stiff, but breaks cleanly. while the rotary safety is a bit stiff to set, but easy enough to disengage, and blocks the trigger and sear from moving, as well as locks the slide, but still allows for the slide to be retracted ust enough for a visual inspection of the chamber. The grips are laminated walnut, and the gun is finished with a corrosion resistant black Teflon coating.  Performance -- Shooting the gun is a pure joy.  The felt recoil is minimal, and the spent rounds eject from the top of the gun, and cycles flawlessly with all types of ammo in general. This particular gun is a bit cosmetically rough, but its meant to be in your pocket, not on display.
